Annex A – Information security controls 
reference 
A.5. Organizational controls 
This section contains all controls that apply across the entire organization, comprising 37 controls, and 
covering: 
● Definition and management of information security policies that support the ISMS; 
● Definition of information security internal organization (e.g., roles, responsibilities, etc.); 
● Consideration of organizational aspects of information security in project management; 
● Identification of information security assets (e.g., information, processing devices, storage 
devices, etc.); 
● Designation of responsibilities for asset security; 
● Knowledge on how to handle responsibilities according to predefined classification levels; 
● Formal processes to grant or revoke access rights; 
● Protection of information that travels through network infrastructure and services; 
● Information security applied to outsourced activities performed by suppliers; 
● Management of information security controls performed by suppliers; 
● Proper communication and handling of security events and incidents; 
● Preservation of evidence as required by business and applicable legal requirements; 
● Improvement of processes to avoid incident recurrence; 
● Continuity of information security management during adverse situations; 
● Prevention of legal, statutory, regulatory, and contractual breaches; 
● Etc. 
For more detail on this subject, take a look at these articles: 
● Information classification according to ISO 27001 
● How to handle access control according to ISO 27001 
● How to handle incidents according to ISO 27001 A.16 
A.6. People controls 
This section focuses on controls related to individual people, comprising eight controls, and covering the 
following topics: 
● Teleworking; 
● Readiness for work and knowledge of information security responsibilities – training & 
awareness; 
● Control of changes in employment conditions that may affect information security.
